  "texts": [
    "How might GenAI impact the externalization of knowledge, and what strategies can be employed to ensure that knowledge management doesn't regress due to duplicated efforts?",
    "Knowledge in organizations is stored in a distributed fashion in individuals' minds, group and social systems, procedures, documents, and computer files.",
    "Tacit knowledge is typically stored within individuals, groups, and organizational culture, whereas explicit knowledge tends to be captured in formal and articulated forms in policies, procedures, and information systems.",
    "Previously, the ability to store organizational knowledge was relatively limited.",
    "It was limited not only by the availability of data itself but also by the type of data."
  ],
